        -- Posted by Neiff on 6:46 pm on May 21, 2001<p>
        Hi Frizzle! <br> <br>All current officers will remain (not smart for the new Guildleader who's coming from a different guild to upset everyone -g-). <br> <br>Belwar's idea was to have 2 officers from each class; I don't like the idea of taking away this status symbol unless it's nessisary, but I do think there needs to be two active officers for each guild to interview/recruit prospective members. Anyone that is currently an officer, but doesn't want to do this, can remain an inactive officer and someone else can take the slot to do the work. <br> <br>In all reality, an officer has one power - to remove and add members to the guild. This is an admin function that can be abused, and if it is abused will end up with the officer being removed. That's the only reason I can think of to remove someone from being an officer, short of just playing at power trips which I'm not interrested in :). <br> <br>This thread has two purposes - let me know who is currently an officer and still wants to do the work, and who is not an officer but would like to be. <br> <br>(Edited by Neiff at 6:46 pm on May 21, 2001)

